Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the study of graphs and their properties, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The algorithms and lower bound constructions mentioned in the paper suggest the involvement of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories.
